{
  "text": "In our approach and in order to model the hydrodynamic flow in the reactor and the short distance between the outlet of the trickling filter and the UV reactor, the average residence time in the irradiation room of the UV reactor is calculated experimentally using the time of passage theoretically observed [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] 50, 60, 70, 80 , and 90 sec) and for all flows tested without resorting to the technique of chemical tracing.",
